Brussel Judoous De Sadeleire
mons. in antwoort aenden ul van 12 deser de groene lakens en sijn noch
niet hier, maer sullen met godts gratie dese naeste weeke hier
sijn als wanneer de selve ul sal toesonden in eenen goede vrapper
ende pack kleet de saper fijn lakens de ul mij geordanneert heeft
te doen koppen sijn al in gekoght ende soo haest die arriveeren
sal ul tlaten weten waer op moght betrouwen midt ick les
@ 16 ditto
Brussel Hendrick de smet
mons Desen tott advies als dat alle mijne goet gearriveert is

Brussel Seger vanderborght
monsr. Desen tot covert van ul facture vande goederen aen ul ve
koght, hebbbe voorde vraght bedongen vant pack sayen ƒ3:10 ende
voort anderpack ƒ2:5 samen ƒ5:15 st ende niet meer moet ul betalen
Icken wil niet eens twijffelen ofte ul sal alles ort contentement
beginden, waer in voorder dinst kan doen gelieft likerlijk te co

Brussel Seb van Homborght
monsr. Desen tot advies als dat alle mijne goederen gearriveert sijn
@ 15 ditto
Brussel Antonio peeters
monsr. Ick en hadde niet getwijffelt oft ul soude volgens ul geloofte
hier gekomen hebbe, d'welke hope niet is whth blen fout
van gesontheyt, soo recommandere ander mael dat ul niet langer
uijt stelt, want ul doet sij selveseer groote pre iuditie met
soo lanck te tardeeren t geene en een weijnigh tijt is te remeditien
en daer en tussche ul broeder tot london moet dat oock door ul
neghoentie bekoopen waghte ul oofte antwoort muna teregateien
Antwerp 18 supsi
Leuven Joan De goede
mons. in antwoort aenden ul gedateert is ang en kan de lakens daer af de
staele hebbe gesonden en kan die niet minder geven als die hebbe gestelt&
aengesien de selve ul maer weijnigh aenstaen soo vinde niet gereden meerder
staelen, te sende oock om dat meestendeel aen ul gesonde hebbe sijn verkoght
soo dat niet beter is als de goederen,: aent stuck te besien sijnde tegenwordigh
uytter metten wel versien van alle sorte, hebbende veel versgoet
ontfang. gelt verwaghte volgens gelofte & blijve

6 16 ditto 1681
th
London John Loys
I had duely recd. yd of 8. past, which I should have answered accordingly
S I ha
butt beeng about a concerne which requited more leasure have informed
mij selfs, as to give you on accompt of mr. moore who hath the whole castle
of Antwarp for his prison & is continually watched with a souldier & very much
suspected, so that itt is very suireey to meddle with him, or to speatto him
he beeng accused by our spanish ambassedor att the hague, as also by severall
mimsters of stato, which he hath abused, yett sir Riold butstroide the kings
resident att Brussels hath acquainted the kingof itt & these on this side
are contented to deliver him so the king of England, where itt seeis
he used no less tricks then here, he is n good health & well disposed & doth
not att all apprehend to suffer, one may see a roogh in his face, he hath
a wise here him a pretty woman, which takes much care for him, butt
in yd letter I finde he hath a wife in England which if should be knouwne
here, would maker him suffer though itt should be upon that accompt
onely: there he ownes no other wife, but that s with him.
as to the annexed note of super scription I do here returne this francois
ofte venson is a fellow which m. moore imployes for receaving & carreing of
. letters & what others he hath occasion for and doth boaid att the house
of mad. Catherune van mill, so in case his wife, or any other doth write
to m moore or northon, lett him send a simple covert over their letter
with samer super sorption, & I do not doubt wrot butt mr. stevenson will
bafely deliver itt now to answer yd of p curitt as to the
legaturen I amsorry the tryall doth not in corridge better this as you say &
yett they can not provide goods enought & do now currantley sell them for ƒ 29:10
e ƒ30: ocp. as to our tykes I assure you I do as much endeavour as anyman can
do to have y. as cheap as possible, yett all I buy & have bought these 3 months
cost 10 stivers a peece more then before & now I have about 200 p. ready to
be packt & send for England, haveing sent above 400 p. more sence I sent yd lasto
& the most part of the higher prive, so that yett there is fast demand
for them where fore in case you please an assortment of 100: or more peeces
lett mee have yd order pr vere first for elce I could not then so soone provide
others because tis now the herveast time & few are made. as to t he
yearne, when the worckmen come totowne shall in forme my selof & give
you an accompt of whilst now I remain
@ 16 Augusti 81
London will Scawen
th
Sr. in answer to yd of 25: past, I can not butt wonder what you say about
the pack of tykes N.16, onely I supose you did take no notice of my letter to
you on the 18 june last which if you please to examin will give you satis=
faction of the contents, yett inclosed yett have an other in voyce & copy
of the said letter, where by you will see the mistake lyes in yd owne neglect
butt not inmine tykes are visen as Itold you & now I have a parcell ready
if you please to have a pack, shall send itt cheaper then any other can
provide itt for you, butt I must have yd answer speedly, other wise should
dispose of them, for they yeald more here then grate them att to you, itt
beeng onelj to make good yd returnes in the callicoes, which for the present
prove a miserable com. becaused in haland is such avast aquantitie arrivee, &
nom will bay, for feare that nexnt sale there will be vrey low so that
I doubt mee must sell to little or no proffitt or lett them ye till next sale
beover, on which yd advise I am a great debter to mr. Henry maynard
so could have wished he was satisfied & you gove will oblige mee to pay some
thing to him the sooner the better, I should draw on you butt dare not without
yd order & the more because I hope mony is come is by this time of what
@ 16 ditto 1681
passes, please to give mee yd advise whilst I rest
Dublin Elnathan Lumm
th
S. in answerd to yd of 19 past I have ready the desired laces, & do not doubt
butt that itt will give incorriggment in order more for now I make itt
much my trade to buy laces & have good comissions from England, so have
provided you from each sort a little which is ready with the mentioned
sereen to be sent to you, exspecting onely the news from holand or bruges
to know which opportunitie of schipping would serve best & according
to which shall send itt next week & give you the advise of as also the
acctts you ordered mee to valew the disbours on mes. de hulter
van homrright which s tell mee to have no advise from you to that
purpose, butt that they have remitted to mr Cole what they will be in
cash againe pr. first which I remaine with kinde salute
I am sorry you should complaine of the tapestry att present such sort yealds
40 stivers an Ell herettis vere scareey & few to be hadd
@ 16 ditto 1681
London Henry Collier
th to 2
S. in answer to yd of 18 & 25 past have accepted yd bill for £150: in favour
of pickering & robinson upon condition of for beurance for I have
no other reason to comply with other correspondents then yd drawing
& I must assure you that though I have goods from H.M for severall
thous and pound, gett have no bills from him up on mee this yeare, &
I love no trade which causeth drawing & redrawing, principally now when
I must fix my creditt & fortune, so I hope you can finde no reason
